LIsp-Flavoured Tensor

further development after the tutorial

run OpenCL code for matmul.model

  # this will generate matmul_cl.h, matmul_cl.c, matmul.cl
  python -m lift --emit opencl --sizes '{ kernel[i] -> grid[2,2]; kernel[i] -> block[2,2]; kernel[i] -> tile[2,2,2]}' matmul matmul.model

  # compile
  gcc -DUSE_OPENCL -o matmul.elf -Wl,--format=binary matmul.cl -Wl,--format=default matmul.c matmul_cl.c -lOpenCL

  # run
  ./matmul.elf


Requirements:

* Python 2.7
* ply (https://pypi.python.org/pypi/ply)
* islpy (https://pypi.python.org/pypi/islpy)
